<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="bacterial_colony">Bacterial Colony</a> - A colony is a point of bacteria growing on a <a href="#petri_dish">Petri dish</a>. If the dishes are prepared correctly then this single point of bacteria should all be issue from the same stock, <em>i.e.</em> one single <a href="#cell">cell</a> was deposited onto the medium and he is the one who <a href="#division">divided</a> in order to produce the others in the colony. All cells in a colony should be genetically identical.